(                   VIII.  VARIATION IN TACTICS\015)'
(\015)'
(\015)'
(     [The heading means literally "The Nine Variations," but as\015)'
(Sun Tzu does not appear to enumerate these, and as,  indeed,  he\015)'
(has already told us \(V SS. 6-11\) that such deflections from the\015)'
(ordinary course are practically innumerable,  we have little\015)'
(option but to follow Wang Hsi, who says that "Nine" stands for an\015)'
(indefinitely large number.  "All it means is that in warfare we\015)'
(ought to very our tactics to the utmost degree....  I do not know\015)'
(what Ts`ao Kung makes these Nine Variations out to be, but it has\015)'
(been suggested that they are connected with the Nine Situations"\015)'
(- of chapt. XI.  This is the view adopted by Chang Yu.  The only\015)'
(other alternative is to suppose that something has been lost--a\015)'
(supposition to which the unusual shortness of the chapter lends\015)'
(some weight.]\015)'
(\015)'
(     1.   Sun Tzu said:   In war,  the general receives his\015)'
(commands from the sovereign, collects his army and concentrates\015)'
(his forces.\015)'
(\015)'
(     [Repeated from VII. ss. 1, where it is certainly more in\015)'
(place.  It may have been interpolated here merely in order to\015)'
(supply a beginning to the chapter.]\015)'
(\015)'
(     2.  When in difficult country, do not encamp.  In country\015)'
(where high roads intersect, join hands with your allies.  Do not\015)'
(linger in dangerously isolated positions.\015)'
(\015)'
(     [The last situation is not one of the Nine Situations as\015)'
(given in the beginning of chap. XI, but occurs later on  \(ibid.\015)'
(ss. 43. q.v.\).  Chang Yu defines this situation as being situated\015)'
(across the frontier, in hostile territory.  Li Ch`uan says it is\015)'
("country in which there are no springs or wells, flocks or herds,\015)'
(vegetables or firewood;" Chia Lin, "one of gorges,  chasms and\015)'
(precipices, without a road by which to advance."]\015)'
(\015)'
(In hemmed-in situations,  you must resort to stratagem.  In\015)'
